Package com.example.vibeverse

Class MoodEvent

java.lang.Object
com.example.vibeverse.MoodEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class MoodEvent extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a mood event recorded by the user.

Each MoodEvent contains details such as the emotional state (with an emoji), an optional trigger, an optional social situation, a formatted timestamp, an intensity level (default is 5), and an optional photograph. A MoodEvent can be converted to/from a Map for storage in Firestore.

      public MoodEvent(String moodTitle, String moodEmoji, String trigger, String socialSituation)
      Constructs a new MoodEvent with the given mood title, emoji, trigger, and social situation. The timestamp is automatically set to the current date and time.
      Parameters:
      moodTitle - The emotional state (e.g., "Happy").
      moodEmoji - The emoji representing the mood.
      trigger - The trigger for the mood.
      socialSituation - The social situation when the mood was recorded.
